  "text": "Skip to main contentWhile each product featured is independently selected by our editors, we may include paid promotion. If you buy something through our links, we may earn commission. Read more about our Product Review Guidelines here.If you're a fan of Reformation, you know it's not every day you find its incredible pieces discounted. The retailer hosts a couple big sales a year, but the coveted pieces sell out fast. Which is why I was totally shocked when I was browsing the sale section at Nordstrom and came across a huge selection of Reformation pieces. There are currently over 20 items marked down, and I could barely contain my excitement. In the assortment were a handful of items I've had my eye on for months, and I quickly snatched them up for up to 55 percent off. Ahead, I curated a list of my nine favorite pieces. Some I just bought and some I already own. So, what are you waiting for? I can tell you sizes are already selling out. Keep reading to shop and snag your favorites before it's too late. nordstrom.comReformation Alex Wide-Leg Linen PantsReformation Alex Wide Leg Linen Pants ($109, originally $198) Who says workwear can't be weekend-worthy? These linen pants are the ultimate chameleon, with a stylish pleated front and comfy wide legs. Wear them everywhere.nordstrom.comReformation Anabella Linen Button-Up TopReformation Anabella Linen Button-Up Top ($111, originally $148) This is a great shirt for those looking to add texture to their look. The romantic linen top has a scalloped lace trim and looks great with a variety of bottoms.nordstrom.comReformation Prim Sleeveless Linen ShirtdressReformation Prim Sleeveless Linen Shirtdress ($158, originally $198) This shirtdress is the perfect option for transitioning from warm days to cozy nights. Pair it with boots and a cardigan for a cozy look or go solo for a chic vibe.nordstrom.comReformation Cary Slouchy Low-Rise Wide-Leg JeansReformation Cary Slouchy Low Rise Wide Leg Jeans ($158, originally $198) Good jeans are hard to find and you'll never look back after trying this Reformation pair. A classic '90s silhouette, the subtle wide leg works for in-office days to weekend brunch and date night.nordstrom.comReformation Layla A-Line Silk SkirtReformation Layla A-Line Silk Skirts ($158, originally $198) This flowy silk skirt is a must have for fall outings (think: apple picking or pumpkin carving). The pull-on waist makes it easy to slip on and off.- Additional reporting by Natasha MarshKrista Jones is a former editor of commerce at PS.Natasha Marsh (she/her) is a freelance writer who writes about fashion, beauty, and lifestyle. Prior to freelancing, she held styling staff positions at The Wall Street Journal, Burberry, Cosmopolitan, British GQ, and Harper's Bazaar.",
